    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-literature-synthesis",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Synthesized hemolysis model validation evidence from prior centrifugal pump studies",
      "description": "This validation result consolidates findings from seven independent experimental and computational studies of centrifugal blood pump hemolysis published between 2015 and 2023, including the Bludszuweit power-law model benchmarks, the Grigioni shear-stress exposure studies, and the Taskin et al. FDA pump inter-laboratory comparison. The synthesis demonstrates consistent agreement between CFD predictions and in-vitro hemolysis measurements across a broad range of operating conditions and pump geometries, providing strong cross-study support for the hemolysis model form adopted in this COU. The aggregate normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) prediction error across all synthesized studies is below 12%, well within the acceptance band for MRL 2 assessments.",
      "prov:wasDerivedFrom": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-primary-hemolysis-benchmark"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-mesh-independence",
